import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('location').mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['location'], data['precipitation'])
    plt.title('What is the average precipitation in each location?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Average Precipitation')
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column=['temp_max', 'temp_min'], by='location', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature in each location?', wrap=True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median temp_max: {data["temp_max"].median():.2f}')
    plt.axhline(y=data['temp_min'].median(), color='b', linestyle='--', label=f'Median temp_min: {data["temp_min"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    data['weekday'] = data['date'].dt.weekday
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].str.capitalize()
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.pivot(index='location', columns='weather', values='counts')
    data = data.fillna(0)
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.axhline(y=data.values.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data.values.max()))
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
